Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: No entry into the FCPC Health Clinic except for any treatment or ailment of defendant.
No entry into the FCPC Health Clinic except for any treatment or ailment of the defendant.

10:05 AM Defendant Jessica A Monnot in court with attorney Robert A Kennedy.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Kennedy and Monnot have complaint, waives reading of it. Kennedy also filed a motion to dismiss the complaint, has no additional information to add. State does have a witness if Court would like to hear testimony. Court - not necessary, will rely on the four corners of the complaint. Court has reviewed the motio, denies the motion for stated reasons. Kennedy enters NG pleas. Court accept plea, continues bond, set for JT. Court adds a condition to the bond of no entry into the FCPC Health Clinic except for any treatment or ailment of the defendant.
Adjourned initial appearance on April 13, 2022 at 10:00 am.

09:37 AM Attorney Robert A Kennedy in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State was advised that the defendant had a mishap this morning and will not be here. Attorney Kennedy confirms, asks for new date. Court continues bond, sets for AIA on 4/13/22 at 10:00 AM.
Adjourned initial appearance on March 16, 2022 at 09:30 am.

09:03 AM Defendant Jessica A Monnot in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin appears by video. CC and CR appear by video. Monnot has received a copy of the complaint. Court reads charge and penalty. Monnot understands. Court questions if she had conntacted an attorney. Monnot has tried to contact SPD, has to get paperwork to them. Court advises if not eligible, can private hire or apply for a court appointed attorney. Monnot understands and will contact SPD. State asks for $100 signature bond. Court will set $100 signature bond. AIA set for 3/16/22 at 9:30 AM.
